The college ground, a rectangular expanse, requires a fence for construction and a carpet for rainy season protection. The management seeks your help to precisely determine the length of the rope needed for the fence and the quantity of carpet required.

Write a program to calculate the exact length of the rope and the necessary carpet quantity based on the provided length and breadth of the ground.

Input Format

The first integer corresponds to the length of the ground. The second integer corresponds to the breadth of the ground.

Constraints

Null

Output Format

Print the results in the specified format.

Sample Input 0

50
20
Sample Output 0

Rope Length: 140m
Carpet Quantity: 1000sqm
Sample Input 1

10
5
Sample Output 1

Rope Length: 30m
Carpet Quantity: 50sqm
Sample Input 2

30
15
Sample Output 2

Rope Length: 90m
Carpet Quantity: 450sqm
Sample Input 3

25
30
Sample Output 3

Rope Length: 110m
Carpet Quantity: 750sqm

import java.io.*;
import java.util.*;

public class Solution {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc=new Scanner(System.in);
        int l=sc.nextInt();
        int b=sc.nextInt();
        int R=2*(l+b);
        int C=l*b;
        System.out.println("Rope Length: "+R+"m");
        System.out.print("Carpet Quantity: "+C+"sqm");
        /* Enter your code here. Read input from STDIN. Print output to STDOUT. Your class should be named Solution. */
    }
}
